snippet.title: Men Having Babies
snippet.description:
Men Having Babies, Inc. is a nonprofit organization that provides educational and practical information to assist gay prospective parents achieve biological parenting. Beyond the organization's world-famous surrogacy conferences for gay men, MHB holds seminars, workshops, and runs several programs including: 
* The Gay Parenting Financial Assistance Program (GPAP) - grants to gay men who require financial assistance in their quest for parenthood. 
* The SurrogacyAdvisor directory of reviews and ratings of agencies and clinics based on real experiences of gay men. 
* A surrogacy Speakers Bureau - over 100 surrogacy parents who are willing to speak to the press about their experiences. 
* The Parent/Peer Advise Network - building a warm community of gay dads who are willing to support each other as well as tell their personal family building story.
